[HEADER]
id: smith_talk
title: The Smith

[CONTENT]
"I can't forge that Iron Key, and I wouldn't if I could," the smith says.
He opens a drawer and sets an old dagger on the bench.
"Lake-steel edge. Bit chipped, still honest."
"Take it. If beasts corner you, don't swing wide. Keep your wrist firm and your feet moving."

